[ a                      owl:Axiom ;
  rdfs:comment           "PMID:2758466 (ES): The glp-1gene is smaller than lin-12 (see Figure 1) and is predicted to encode a smaller primary translation product (1295 \nversus 1429 amino acids). Corresponding exons in the two genes average \n50% nucleotide sequence identity and require little gapping to optimize \nalignments. " , "PMID:18700817 (ES): The LAG-2 and DSL-1 interactions with LIN-12 in the two-hybrid assay are consistent with previous genetic studies in\nC. elegans and with biochemical analyses of Notch ligand/receptor\ninteractions in other systems. " ;
